Break Statement 

It will terminate the loop.  After break keyword we can not write the code, it will give compile time error. Becasue the code which is after break keyword is unreachable. 
Break statement will terminate the nearest loop. If you use break inside the inner loop it will only break the inner, outer loop will continue to run. 


"terminate"

take all chars from string and print only first matching e from given string. 


Continue Statement 
1- Continue statement will not break the loop but it will skip the current iteration and continue from the next iteration
2- After continue statement you can not write the code, since it will be unreachable statement
3- Continue statement will skip the iteration for nearest loop

























